//	$(".thecontent").fadeOut('fast');	createball();});	$('.ui-accordion').bind('accordionchange', function(event, ui) {//	$(".thecontent").fadeIn('fast');});			});</script></head><body><style>html{overflow-y: scroll;}body{overflow-x:hidden;}p{text-indent:1em;}.floatright{float:right;clear:none;display:block;}#addcredidation{line-height:2;}#resumeholder {margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;width:0px;border: 1px solid black;overflow:none;position:relative;z-index:200;background: white;}#resumecontent {opacity:0;position:relative;width:580px;overflow:auto;margin:10px;margin-top:50px;/* border: 0px solid black;border-bottom: 2px black solid; */}  #resumeheader {/*margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;overflow:none;*/border-bottom: 1px solid black;width:580px;position:absolute;display:none;}span{display:inline-block;}.slider{font-size:36px;font-family: "sans-serif";display:none;clear:none;float:left;}.historyp{margin-top:0px;}.center{text-align:center;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;}.ball{position:fixed;z-index:100;cursor: pointer;}#resumeheader{cursor:pointer;}</style>	<div id="resumeholder">		<div id="resumeheader">			<span class="slider">&nbsp;B</span><span class="slider">r</span><span class="slider">a</span><span class="slider">n</span><span class="slider">d</span><span class="slider">o</span><span class="slider">n&nbsp;</span><span class="slider">S</span><span class="slider">e</span><span class="slider">l</span><span class="slider">w</span><span class="slider">a</span><span class="slider">y</span>				<span class="slider" style="float:right; font-size:18px;text-align:right;"><i>443-564-8729<br>brandon.selway@gmail.com</i></span>						</div>			<div id="resumecontent">		   <h3><a href="#">Overview</a></h3>		   <div><div class="thecontent">				<p>A lifelong programming hobbyist, meta-analyst, and self-styled minimalist who finds beauty in doing the most with the least;</p>				<p>Always searching for underlying logic behind systems in order to extend their function beyond standard capacity;</p>				<p>Enthusiast of language: from the musical to the scientific, from computer to spoken, all provide insight to the process of creation and meaning;</p>				<p>Fully engages the everpresent necessity to interweave diverse perspectives into deeper layers of significance.</p>				<p>Takes pride in an endless desire to learn and explore, boundless self-motivation, unshakable stability, and modesty within self-confidence.</p>				<p>&nbsp;</p>				<ul id="accredidation">					<li>BS in Electronic Media and Film at Towson University, Magna Cum Laude</li>					<li>8+ years professional and academic in web programming / motion graphics</li>					<li>Strong in dynamic, nonstandard User Interface development.</li>				</ul>		   </div></div>		   <h3><a href="#">Experience</a></h3>		   <div><div class="thecontent">				<p></p>				Extensive:<br>				<ul>					<li>PHP / MySQL</li>					<li>Javascript / jQuery / Node.js</li>					<li>CSS / Custom Theming (General)</li>					<li>CMS implementation / modification</li>					<li>Video Compositing (Adobe After Effects)</li>					<li>3d Modeling and Scripting (3d Studio Max)</li>				</ul>			   Secondary:<br>			   <ul>					<li>ExtJS / Sencha Touch</li>					<li>NoSQL (MongoDB, CouchDB)</li>					<li>Tinkerpop GraphDB suite</li>					<li>Canvas / WebGL / SVG</li>					<li>Google Apps/Facebook OpenGraph</li>					<li>Python / Twisted</li>					<li>LAMP administration</li>				</ul>		   </div></div>		   <h3><a href="#">History</a></h3>		   <div><div class="thecontent">		   <span class="floatright">October 2010 - Present</span>					<b>Various</b>				<p class="historyp">Freelance work / consulting on a variety of projects, development of APIs with Node.js, integration with APIs of various Google Applications.  Volunteering help with a non-profit Permaculture Institute.</p><span class="floatright">October 2009 - October 2010</span>					<b>TheNext.Us - <i>Lead Developer</i></b>				<p class="historyp">Designed, from scratch, a social networking website fully utilizing: the Jquery javascript library, latest AJAX techniques, custom Linux InspirCD chat server including C++ modules, customized Python qwebirc webchat-interface, CSS/webkit/cross-browser styling, extensive custom PHP/Mysql and Javascript functionality.</p><span class="floatright">October 2006 - May 2008</span>					<b>Eyemaginations Inc. - <i>Animator</i></b>				<p class="historyp">Advanced skills with animation and programming using both 3d and compositing programs, edited hundreds of videos, designed animations for cutting-edge medical animation (ophthalmology) software, custom algorithms for 3d Studio Max's propriatary language MaxScript.</p><span class="floatright">January 2004 - January 2007</span>					<b>Towson University - <i>Electronic Media & Film Student</i></b>				<p class="historyp">Focus on digital effects including the use of custom algorithms for image, video, and sound processing.</p><span class="floatright">March 2003 - March 2004</span>					<b>ccTransact Inc. - <i>Webmaster</i></b>				<p class="historyp">In charge of LAMP administration, PHP development, upgrade and maintenance of client pages and company webserver.</p>		   </div></div>		   <h3><a href="#"><b>Portfolio</b></a></h3>		   <div><div class="thecontent">		   <a>NDA protected web app</a>		   <p>Nearly complete single-page web app that is built entirely out of novel, cutting edge web tech:  ExtJS (via Sencha Architect) for the client side, Node.js for the back end API, and MongoDB for persistent data-store.  Working on this project has been an education in itself, and is an example of what I personally find thrilling about the field of web development.		   </p>		   <a href="http://telekritika.ge/">Telekritika.ge</a>		   <p>Telekritika is a civilian news-monitoring social network built for Transparency International Georgia, ontop of the Elgg PHP framework and extensively leveraging the jQuery Javascript library.  In order to implement complex features, Elgg had to be heavily modified and customized in order to allow: queuing and consolidating of UI events and AJAX requests; realtime interaction with the backend components of the site; internationalization with crowdsourced translation elements; deep facebook integration via Open Graph; complex ranking algorithms for measuring popularity vs. controversy vs. quantitative contribution; and a complex "channelviewer" mini-app, in which large amounts of data must be parsed through and interacted with in a smooth and intuitive fashion.  Clever data-binding and UX/UI development are the most novel features of this site.</p>		   		   <a href="http://sexdiariesproject.com/">The Sex Diaries Project</a><p>Overhauled novel anonymous diaries project for author Arianne Cohenne. Implemented PR site, email campaigns, and new features including optimization of PHP / MySQL back-end, extensive AJAX / jQuery implementation, internationalization, and security.</p>					<a href="http://peaceinbaltimore.com">Peace in Baltimore</a>				<p>Fully AJAX/Jquery powered website using a custom developed theme that optimizes and reroutes basic functions of wordpress while retaining ease-of-use for client on the backend.  Aesthetics of the UI and design are integrated seemlessly to give the overall experience of flow in browsing.  Leverages Google Calendar API to allow for ease of dynamic scheduled events.</p>					<a href="http://mywedding.com/blog/">Delightfully Engaged</a>				<p>Emphasis here on CSS, Jquery, and PHP Wordpress API tricks to implement a more-than-meets-the-eye blog featuring: slideshows, custom image galleries, variety of modified / custom plugins, complex menu and submenu selection, custom styled dropdown menus, and much more.  All while remaining dynamic and updateable by client.</p>					<a href="http://mywedding.com/blog/planning/">Resource Guide</a>				<p>Site requiring multiple cross-domain embeds, custom but flexible categorization, menus, etc.</p>					<a href="http://reservation-telephone.com/">Reservation Telephone Company</a>				<p>Contracted to develop a variety of plugins for this site including a CSV import utility, a dynamic slideshow creator, and others.</p>				<p>DVD Reel of animation available on request</p>		   </div></div>		   <h3><a href="#">References</a></h3>		   <div>				<div class="thecontent">		   					<span class="floatright">Nate Guisinger</span>						<i>Professional Developer</i>					<p>917.407.8610</p>						<span class="floatright">Gustavo Lanzas & Associates</span>						Gustavo Lanzas - <i>Owner / President</i>					<p>415.845.9249</p>						<span class="floatright">The Portland Company</span>						Spencer Hill - <i>Owner / President</i>					<p>503.933.4815</p>						<span class="floatright">Science Integration Institute</span>						Todd Duncan - <i>Co-founder</i>					<p>503.805.7860</p>				</div>		   </div>		</div>	</div><script>	$("#resumeholder").animate({width:"600px"},{duration:1000, complete: function(){			$("#resumecontent").animate({opacity:1},{duration:1000, complete: function(){								$("#resumeheader").show();				  $(".slider:eq(0)").show("fast", function(){						$(this).next(".slider").slideDown(150,arguments.callee);					});				}			});		}	});</script>		</body></html>